SIMPLE: group
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Group
<hw>Group</hw> <pr>(gr⟦oomac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F
<ets>groupe</ets>, It. <ets>gruppo</ets>, <ets>groppo</ets>, cluster,
bunch, packet, group; of G. origin: cf. G. <ets>kropf</ets> craw, crop,
tumor, bunch. See <er>Crop</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
cluster, crowd, or throng; an assemblage, either of persons or things,
collected without any regular form or arrangement; <as>as, a
<ex>group</ex> of men or of trees; a <ex>group</ex> of
isles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An assemblage of objects in a certain order or
relation, or having some resemblance or common characteristic; <as>as,
<ex>groups</ex> of strata</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A variously limited assemblage of
animals or plants, having some resemblance, or common characteristics in
form or structure. The term has different uses, and may be made to
include certain species of a genus, or a whole genus, or certain genera,
or even several orders.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A number of eighth, sixteenth,
etc., notes joined at the stems; -- sometimes rather indefinitely
applied to any ornament made up of a few short notes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Group</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Group
<hw>Group</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Grouped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Grouping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>grouper</ets>. See
<er>Group</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To form a group of; to arrange
or combine in a group or in groups, often with reference to mutual
relation and the best effect; to form an assemblage of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The difficulty lies in drawing and disposing, or, as the painters
term it, in <qex>grouping</qex> such a multitude of different
objects.</q> <rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grouped columns</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>three
or more columns placed upon the same pedestal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>grouped</ent>⟦br⟧
